<li id="cite_note-34"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-34">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation magazine cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20081205015754/http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,791839,00.html">"A Century of Progress"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Time_(magazine)" title="Time (magazine)">Time</a></i>. January 1, 1945. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,791839,00.html">the original</a> on December 5, 2008<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">July 15,</span> 2008</span>. <q>Present editor and publisher (third in the line) is Orson Desaix Munn, 61, a patent lawyer, crack bird hunter and fisherman, rumba fancier, familiar figure in Manhattan café society.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Time&amp;rft.atitle=A+Century+of+Progress&amp;rft.date=1945-01-01&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.time.com%2Ftime%2Fmagazine%2Farticle%2F0%2C9171%2C791839%2C00.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AScientific+American" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-A_History_of_American_Magazines-35"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-A_History_of_American_Magazines_35-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="Mott,_A_History_of_American_Magazines" class="citation book cs1">Mott, Frank Luther (1970) [1938]. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=lm7rSZ2BoK8C&amp;q=scientific+american+Charles+Allen+Munn+editor&amp;pg=PA316"><i>A History of American Magazines, 1850–1865</i></a> (4th&#160;ed.). London: Oxford University Press. p.&#160;316. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-674-39551-0" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-674-39551-0"><bdi>978-0-674-39551-0</bdi></a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">August 9,</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+History+of+American+Magazines%2C+1850%E2%80%931865&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pages=316&amp;rft.edition=4th&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=1970&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-674-39551-0&amp;rft.aulast=Mott&amp;rft.aufirst=Frank+Luther&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3Dlm7rSZ2BoK8C%26q%3Dscientific%2Bamerican%2BCharles%2BAllen%2BMunn%2Beditor%26pg%3DPA316&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AScientific+American" class="Z3988"></span></span>
